WEBVTT

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:01.976
whether that part exists or not.

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:06.256
That believes the thoughts are sometimes
its own and sometimes not.

00:05:06.280 --> 00:05:13.770
So according to Buddhism there is no “I”.

00:05:14.200 --> 00:05:20.296
The interaction of the components
that make up the mind and the body

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:24.016
creates a feeling of permanence,
which is self.

00:05:24.040 --> 00:05:27.096
According to one perspective of Hinduism,

00:05:27.321 --> 00:05:32.040
the self is an all-encompassing
consciousness